{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"pale-fist-prow","description":"# Engine-wide caching: extend the runner cache to RunnerAgentStep (all workflow agent steps)\n\n## Why\nS1 caches plan-review's Pass-1 calls. The same stable-prefix waste exists in every workflow agent step\n(verify/decide/coach/grounding) and other workflows (completion-verification, code-review) — they re-send a\nstable system prompt + tool surface across runs. Extending caching there is the engine-wide win pulled into scope.\n\n## What\n- In the engine `RunnerAgentStep` (`workflow/runs.py:207`, builds RunRequest), populate S1's cacheable-prefix\n  boundary: the static system prompt (+ stable inputs) is the cached prefix; per-run ticket data is the\n  volatile suffix.\n- Add a prompt-model convention to mark which part of an assembled workflow prompt is the byte-stable prefix vs\n  per-run volatile inputs, so the boundary is set generically (not per call site).\n- Apply `anthropic_cache_instructions` for the system prompt across steps; keep dynamic per-run content OUT of\n  the cached prefix (after the CachePoint / a separate message part).\n\n## Scope\n- In: RunnerAgentStep prefix wiring; the prompt-model stable-vs-volatile convention; applying to all workflows.\n- Out: the runner mechanism itself (S1, dependency); container parallelization (S3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] RunnerAgentStep populates the cacheable prefix; verify/decide/coach cache their stable system-prompt/tool\n      prefix on anthropic (`cache_read > 0` on repeats), unchanged on other providers.\n- [ ] completion-verification and code-review workflows benefit (cache reads non-zero on repeats).\n- [ ] Per-run volatile inputs are excluded from the cached prefix (stability test).\n- [ ] `make lint` + tests pass; no finding change.\n","id":"c6e5-9936-d07c-4b16","parent_id":"c81c-cbcd-17a0-43d2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Engine-wide caching: extend the runner cache to RunnerAgentStep (all workflow agent steps)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782543568060122001,"uuid":"793c05c5-a094-405b-a0db-01e94e16b5d7"}